@node MAIN "Welcome"

@{fg shine}----------------------------------------------------------------@{fg text}
                                     @{fg fill}A U T O C H E C K . M D R X@{fg text}
@{fg text}---------------------------------------------------------------- @{fg text}


Author:   Dave Crawford "Targhan"

Purpose:  Re-enable AutoChecking of email in versions of MD2 > 1.4.4

Requires: Working ARexx, the Wait command, and MorphOS or AmigaOS.

Type:     comm/mail

Long:     Welcome to Autocheck and Autocheck-news for MicroDot2.
          If you use MicroDot2, you are probably still using version
          1.4.4 because any newer version has a broken "autocheck"
          for email.  Well, this arexx script fixes that little problem,
          and a second script gives that same functionality to the NNTP
          portion of MicroDot2.


@{fg shine}----------------------------------------------------------------@{fg text}
                                     @{fg fill}A U T O C H E C K . M D R X@{fg text}
@{fg text}---------------------------------------------------------------- @{fg text}



Installation: Simply copy the two mdrx files into your MicroDot/Rexx
          directory, or if you use MDMaster, copy them to MicroDot/MDRexx.

Configuration: At the top of each mdrx file there is a variable for the
          number of seconds to wait before checking for email/news.

                             "checktime = 120"

          Simply change the value to match the interval you prefer
          between mail/news checks. Save the file. The defaults are
          120 for email (autocheck.mdrx), which is 2 minutes, and 300
          for news (autocheck-news.mdrx), which is 5 minutes.

          Also, you may have to quit and restart MD2 for the scanner
          to locate the ARexx scripts (does not apply to MDMaster).

Starting:
         1. No MDMaster: Simply select autocheck.mdrx or
         autocheck-news.mdrt from the menu.  Note: multiple
         (more than two) #?.mdrx files in the Rexx directory
         of MicroDot2 has been known to cause problems with
         certain releases.  If you have any more mdrx scripts
         in the Rexx directory, it is suggested that you install
         MDMaster.

         2. MDMaster: Select MDMaster from the Rexx pull-down menu.
         Then, select the script you wish to start from the requester
         as above.  If you actually have to use the search feature of
         MDMaster, please let me know :-)  I've not seen THAT many
         mdrx scripts!

Exiting: Exiting the autochecker is as simple as closing MicroDot2's
         window.


